	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45448567"><p><div class="quote"><p>Follow the money.  Is there any money for the tele-sales companies, or phone the companies, to prevent phone calls from taking place?</p></div><p>Yes.  It costs money to make the calls, and it is especially expensive to deal with jerks like me that <i>always</i> press one to get a live operator, pretend to be very interested in the product, agree to place an order, and then give them a sequence of made up credit card numbers until they finally hang up.  I make a game out of keeping them on the line as long as possible.  My record is 43 minutes.  If they filtered out my number it would save them a lot of money.</p><p>Yes, I am already on the national-do-not-call-list, but I still get a few auto-calls almost everyday.</p></div>
	</div>

