	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45448247"><p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special_information_tones" title="wikipedia.org" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special_information_tones</a> [wikipedia.org]</p><p>Still works, I use the 'service disconnected' SIT code as the opening to my voicemail message.  Pretty much stops spam after the first call.  The SIT codes are very timing and tone sensitive, so you need a good recording and to be able to upload a file for your voicemail message rather than trying to record it with the phone mic.</p></div>
	</div>

