	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_45448601">So you have your voicemail answer after 3 or less rings? Because the telemarketer systems all hang up on the 4th ring so they don't get your voice message unless you set the ring count for answering under 4. You'll generally find that any calls that go on past 4 rings are not your normal telemarketing. They might be calls you don't want, but they usually are not an autodialer type telemarketing scheme.<br> <br>Of course the "do not call" list was supposed to protect those in the US from this crap already. It worked</div>
	</div>

